</title>
<subSubSection id="7299622E949D96DE20C9409DCEF85B8D" pageId="null" pageNumber="480" type="description">
<paragraph id="DBB1788873C474A8D881CC51235160D7" pageId="null" pageNumber="480">
10-40 cm hoch; Horste, 
<normalizedToken id="CA0FE461E337011650C8BCC3AD6DE25D" originalValue="Ausläufer" pageId="null" pageNumber="480">Auslaeufer</normalizedToken>
und 
<normalizedToken id="26E0577128ED6C9AF7879B0A5C49FE4D" originalValue="grundständige" pageId="null" pageNumber="480">grundstaendige</normalizedToken>
, blattlose Scheiden wie bei 
<taxonomicName id="2C33F7D561B0BC2F5A9D05C1827D37D3" class="Liliopsida" family="Cyperaceae" genus="Carex" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="null" pageNumber="480" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ferruginea">
<emphasis id="2D76D85482C7BB5BDF2EAEEBBDFDBBB8" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="480">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="9D9B02C14864AA7E555AB752F0B39C3E" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="480">ferruginea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Nr. 84) (ohne Faserschopf). 
<normalizedToken id="905076C265543D69D27F89982C12A558" originalValue="Blätter" pageId="null" pageNumber="480">Blaetter</normalizedToken>
2-3 mm breit, 
<emphasis id="76F8E1339DAB4A64B3459D88DAF7BA7E" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="480">flach, steif</emphasis>
, den 
<normalizedToken id="854C3AEE335F9E19C5FA5A5DC673C7BF" originalValue="Blütenstand" pageId="null" pageNumber="480">Bluetenstand</normalizedToken>
nicht erreichend. Stengel scharf 3kantig, rauh. 
<normalizedToken id="FCC6EFBC3113C51E6510A511CB562FD8" originalValue="Blütenstand" pageId="null" pageNumber="480">Bluetenstand</normalizedToken>
im Habitus 
<normalizedToken id="9954A8A6AC943FFFB8C485E5379D4968" originalValue="ähnlich" pageId="null" pageNumber="480">aehnlich</normalizedToken>
<taxonomicName id="7CE956FE0FA6830D6E3AB6ADD013ED8F" class="Liliopsida" family="Cyperaceae" genus="Carex" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="null" pageNumber="480" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ferruginea">
<emphasis id="42DBA7BBD33D575AF18BD9A36FC2528F" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="480">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="57469921DE48AE8B9FAB8EBD0C156D3C" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="480">ferruginea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, die ♀ 
<normalizedToken id="49C786BEE684BF8D74139BD3A9BADC4E" originalValue="Ähren" pageId="null" pageNumber="480">Aehren</normalizedToken>
jedoch oft nur kurz gestielt und 
<emphasis id="964CA22AC7294E3F6D86E20177A5F0ED" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="480">stets aufrecht.</emphasis>
<normalizedToken id="49D97930BE4E54974483E927D6D0BFFD" originalValue="Tragblätter" pageId="null" pageNumber="480">Tragblaetter</normalizedToken>
wie bei 
<emphasis id="FC6FDC34E750DFF51522606C8E834808" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="480">
<taxonomicName id="D481320B15B0D9884D631115CE5B9FD5" class="Liliopsida" family="Cyperaceae" genus="Carex" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="null" pageNumber="480" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ferruginea">C. ferruginea</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
<normalizedToken id="AB9B0891692A9D01884B672CE848D1F2" originalValue="Fruchtschläuche" pageId="null" pageNumber="480">Fruchtschlaeuche</normalizedToken>
in 
<normalizedToken id="F72C7BB490EDB507FD47E1C5DE3581DC" originalValue="Größe" pageId="null" pageNumber="480">Groesse</normalizedToken>
, Form, Farbe und Glanz wie bei 
<taxonomicName id="CB99DECAB943D119D2A672CAF826B779" authority="Nerven" authorityName="Nerven" class="Liliopsida" family="Cyperaceae" genus="Carex" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="null" pageNumber="480" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ferruginea">
<emphasis id="2B03EE518C120CD2F13814AE98F6360F" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="480">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="D46AB28B8200ECC1EE51A27270F49400" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="480">ferruginea, Nerven jedoch deutlicher.</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Narben 3.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F31C2582FF20094840C84CCAFF17E0D4" pageId="null" pageNumber="480">
<emphasis id="6191A16B5B7A3C323CB3DD600A8F0777" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="480">Zytologische Angaben.</emphasis>
Keine Untersuchungen.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AE24167C04CD49F340E557775FD742AD" pageId="null" pageNumber="480">
<emphasis id="B355099B5C636BC718886B70A597EA0F" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="480">Standort.</emphasis>
Alpin. Feuchte Felsspalten.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6078678CD0D5D418D250A0F88F019631" pageId="null" pageNumber="480">
<emphasis id="42FA4A79F90A42EE361511D30A731AB1" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="480">Verbreitung. Mittelalpenpflanze:</emphasis>
Grajische, Penninische und 
<normalizedToken id="7BB5E9FC22E5044A90DB0D9B4C7F1D4B" originalValue="Rhätische" pageId="null" pageNumber="480">Rhaetische</normalizedToken>
Alpen. Im Gebiet: Wenige Fundstellen in Savoyen und im Aostatal, Val de Bagnes und Gebiet von Zermatt (Wallis), 
<normalizedToken id="0EE61008DD643EA2C69A04E3C0B42143" originalValue="Cancianopaß" pageId="null" pageNumber="480">Cancianopass</normalizedToken>
im Puschlav (
<normalizedToken id="E8BF975A83174C01784AA886FAC1B6B7" originalValue="Graubünden" pageId="null" pageNumber="480">Graubuenden</normalizedToken>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
